The probability associated with each of the four sample points is $\frac{1}{4}$. Identifying the probabilities of the sample points associated with each of these values of $x$, we have:

$$
\begin{aligned}
P(x=0)=P(T T) & =\frac{1}{4} \\
P(x=1)=P(T H)+P(H T) & =\frac{1}{4}+\frac{1}{4}=\frac{1}{2} \\
P(x=2)=P(H H) & =\frac{1}{4}
\end{aligned}
$$
